<section class="section" id="about">
	<div class="container background-greyscale">
	
		<h2 class="text-center title">About Touch Rugby</h2>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-sm-4 col-sm-offset-2">    
				<h5><strong>What is Touch Rugby?<br></strong></h5>
				<p>Touch rugby (also known as “touch”) is a minimal contact sport that is played worldwide by men, women and children of all ages. The game emphasizes running, agility and ball handling skills such as passing and catching.</p>    
			</div>
			<div class="col-sm-4">
				<h5><strong>Who can play?<br></strong></h5>    
				<p>Due to the minimal contact aspect, Touch Rugby is much more mixed in gender. Rugby players are usually guys, but in Touch Rugby it’s completely mixed. Girls and guys will play in the same team, guys can play against girls. Both sexes can play with and against each other, and it’s really common for that to happen too.</p>    
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="row">
		  <div class="col-sm-4 col-sm-offset-2">
		    <h5><strong>How serious is Touch Rugby?<br></strong></h5>    
			  <p>The great thing about Touch is that you can play to any level you want, most clubs play socially and competitively. Using this site you can find out what clubs are near you and to what level they play too. Touch is all about getting everyone involved.</p>    
		  </div>
		  <div class="col-sm-4">
		    <h5><strong>Do I need any special equipment?<br></strong></h5>    
			  <p>Comfortable clothing is recommended, shorts, t-shirts etc. Footwear would include trainers or boots. Please note NO screw-ins or metal studs are allowed.</p>    
		  </div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<!-- Third (affiliation) section -->
<section class="section" id="affiliation">
